title: David Healy hopes Northern Irish triumph can heal old wounds - York Press
text:
Healy is the nation's most beloved player of recent times, having notched an unrivalled 36 goals including the winner against England in 2005 and a hat-trick versus Spain the following year. He was at Windsor Park to see the current generation seal their place at Euro 2016 with a fine 3-1 win over Greece on Thursday and feels the achievement can have a wider significance for the nation.
 York Press.
